OL,3,CThousands of drivers wrongly fined for
OL,4,Cspeeding since 2021 due to faulty
OL,5,Ccameras
OL,7,FThousands of people could have their
OL,8,Fspeeding fines cancelled after it was
OL,9,Ffound that a "technical issue"
OL,10,Fincorrectly triggered speed cameras.
OL,12,FA software update is believed to have
OL,13,Fcaused faults in variable speed
OL,14,Fcameras on some A roads and motorways,
OL,15,Fwrongly flagging drivers as speeding
OL,16,Fafter the speed limit had increased.
OL,18,FNational Highways said a "very small
OL,19,Fnumber" of drivers had been fined
OL,20,Fincorrectly since 2021, and apologised
OL,21,Ffor the error.
